This abstract class represents a basic model for objects on a canvas, providing properties such as coordinates, width, and height.

This abstract class represents a clickable button that can be interacted with in a graphical user interface.

The Drawable interface represents an object that can be drawn on a graphical context.

The GameController class controls the main functionality of the SnakeGame after the menu screen.

The GameUtil class provides utility methods for handling game-related tasks, such as loading images, rotating images, tinting images, and creating styled buttons.
ImageUtil
The ImageUtil class provides utility methods for loading images used in the game.

This abstract class extends the basic canvas object model to include a state indicating whether the object is alive or not.

The Main class serves as the entry point for the SnakeGame application.

The MusicPlayer class provides functionality for playing background music in the game.
